title.narrative: 4.2. PREVENTION AND EARLY INTERVENTION

description.narrative: Government and civil society have strengthened capacities to provide prevention and early intervention services to all vulnerable children, including children with disabilities, children on the move and under emergency situations., which contributes to Prevention Of Harmful Practice, Promotion Of Care, Mental Health And Psychosocial Well-Being And Justice, Protection From Violence, Exploitation, Abuse And Neglect. UNICEF aims to achieve this through Advocacy And Public Engagement, Community Engagement, Social And Behaviour Change, Developing And Leveraging Resources And Partnerships, Evaluations, Research And Data, Partnerships And Engagement: Public And Private, Systems Strengthening And Institution Building, Systems Strengthening To Leave No One Behind, United Nations Working Together. This contributes to the following Country Programme result: Girls and boys, especially the most marginalized, receive multi-sectoral preventive and response services, care and social assistance within their homes, schools and communities.

description.narrative: Community Based Prevention and early intervention programmes were consolidated in 2021 leading to the launch of the Risiha Programme. The Risiha programme is a ;government programme aimed at moving children from vulnerability to resilience. UNICEF continued to support the use of innovation to support families creating an environment for gender responsive care. Great progress is being achieved towards the social compact, a partnership between government, UNICEF and corporate for prevention and early interventions services with more resources coming in from corporate South Africa towards Prevention and Early Intervention ;services. | Status:On-track | As-of Date:05/01/2022
